    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But you cry what you went through and you laugh for what it is now.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then it started already.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then they were all-- the people from had first acceptance or first-- they were in queue the first to go to Israel, because this was not anything illegal anymore.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And unfortunately I must say-- unfortunately, a lot of young people that were on coming to Israel, because they were the first to come to Israel, were sent to Latrun.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Latrun was a colossal battle with the-- the English and the Arabs.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The English [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] left and [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And a lot of people were killed in Latrun.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We arrived in Israel in May 1949.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
